  "body": "\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \r\nWhen the user wants to send a transaction to a new recipient the screen flickers when trying to add a new user using the QR code, the error message Invalid address is displayed.\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nUsers should not see the screen flickering when adding a new contact usong the QR code.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nThe screen flickers when users scan the QR code.\r\n\r\n![image 3](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/33925578/35221554-75a162b2-ff72-11e7-92da-350aa31a7c54.png)\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- As user 1, open Status using the iPhone SE.\r\n- As user 2, open Status using the Samsung Galaxy S6 (user 2 wallet is not empty).\r\n- As user 1 navigate to the user profile and display the QR code.\r\n- As User 2, select the \"Wallet\", seledt \"Sen transaction\", tap the \"recipient\" and scan user 1 QR code, notice the screen flickers and the error message is displayed. (The screen does not flicker when scanning with the iPhone).\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: \r\nReal Galaxy S6, status version 0.9.10-600-g54e83c58+\r\nReal iphone SE status version 0.9.12 (testFlight)\r\n* Operating System: Android 6.0.1, iOS: 11.2.2\r\n\r\n",
